about.summary: Multiple pairwise comparison tests for one-way analysis of variance for both between-subjects and within-subjects designs. Currently, it supports only the most common types of statistical analyses and tests: parametric (Welch's and Student's t-test), nonparametric (Durbin-Conover test and Dwass-Steel-Crichtlow-Fligner test), robust (Yuenâ€™s trimmed means test).

name: r-pairwisecomparisons
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.1.0' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-pairwisecomparisons
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/pairwiseComparisons_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/pairwiseComparisons/pairwiseComparisons_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: f39cf8e9c8adb0b5876bad4ac9429f7aabd27a7be6ef629319f36efaa4b261a2

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{posix}}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-wrs2 >=1.0_0
    - r-broomextra >=0.0.5
    - r-crayon >=1.3.4
    - r-dplyr >=0.8.3
    - r-forcats
    - r-groupedstats
    - r-jmv
    - r-magrittr >=1.5
    - r-purrrlyr
    - r-rlang >=0.4.0
    - r-stringr
    - r-tibble >=2.1.3
    - r-tidyr >=0.8.3
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-wrs2 >=1.0_0
    - r-broomextra >=0.0.5
    - r-crayon >=1.3.4
    - r-dplyr >=0.8.3
    - r-forcats
    - r-groupedstats
    - r-jmv
    - r-magrittr >=1.5
    - r-purrrlyr
    - r-rlang >=0.4.0
    - r-stringr
    - r-tibble >=2.1.3
    - r-tidyr >=0.8.3

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('pairwiseComparisons')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('pairwiseComparisons')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://indrajeetpatil.github.io/pairwiseComparisons/, https://github.com/IndrajeetPatil/pairwiseComparisons
  license: GPL-3
  summary: "Multiple pairwise comparison tests for one-way analysis of variance for both between-subjects
    and within-subjects designs. Currently, it supports only the most common types of
    statistical analyses and tests: parametric (Welch's and Student's t-test), nonparametric
    (Durbin-Conover test and Dwass-Steel-Crichtlow-Fligner test), robust (Yuen\xE2\u20AC\u2122s
    trimmed means test)."
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
